Hopefully this random thought/messages will inspire some one. You are in fact in charge of your life and happiness. Don't regret the things that's happened. Learn from it and be a better person because of it! You are successful! You got this! Keep going! (15 of 15)

I need to stop waiting for good things to happen and just go out and take it for myself! Worry less and live every day to the fullest. Hopefully I can remember this lesson when I'm feeling down again. 🤣  (14 of 15)

I have succeded in life, I over came my anxiety and became a better person and am able to communicate. I have built a good life, friends, family and community. I kept waiting for things to get better. But I realized they already were! (13 of 15)

I realized my memories are still there they are just stored. Remembering all of this has made me realize, I thought I hadn't lived life at all since I couldn't remember anything. But I have lived a good life and I need to stop worrying about getting older. (12 of 15)

I have a good job where I can communicate to all my customers and co-workers. I have successfully built a community while streaming as well as making some amazing friends along the way! And a happy relationship I never thought I would have. (11 of 15)

I can carry on a full conversation with strangers!! Hell I did this just the other day at the store. I got through all of those rough times and I'm here today! I was bullied as a teen by my friends but I came out stronger! I am successful. (10 of 15)

I had "Selective Mutism" look it up. It's a social anxiety disorder that pervents me from communicating properly. As I realized how much I struggled in school and thought I would never make it through. Look where I am today!! (9 of 15)

I started remembering things I had long forgotten. Granted not all of it was good. Some of it bad, but I realized something. Let me give a short backstory here. I went to school from kindergarten to 4th. I was then homeschooled from 4th until I got my GED (8 of 15)

I think that's why I've been a bit depressed lately. I mean what have I really done in 30 years? Well going back and starting journaling from the beginning has taught me something. I made myself happy today. My memories are still there! (7 of 15)

Though I stopped mentally growing around 18, I haven't felt my age since then, is what I mean. I realized my life has gone by in a huge blink. I haven't done anything with my life!!! I haven't become successful in the things I wanted to. (6 of 15)

I was sadden by this, I couldn't remember the good times nor could I remember the bad. It was both a blessing and a curse. I became a bit more depressed when I realized this. Turning 30 hit me harder then it should have because of this. (5 of 15)

Point is, from the age of 4 or 5 since my memories started developing, I wanted to write them down at least what I could remember. I've dealt with depression since the age of 12. Most my memories from 12 and back are gone! I've lost all memories or so I thought. (4 of 15)

I sometimes am an open book to my community and my friends. Most times I'm a closed book. I didn't want to burden any more people with my problems as I've had friends abandoned me cause I'm "too depressing" so I'm making a journal. (3 of 15)

I started journaling again the other day. I missed it, I use to want to write but never trusted the people around me not to read it or look over my shoulder. I started from the beginning. I wanted to get every thought out of my head and off my chest from age 5 to now. (2 of 15)

So I feel like I had an epiphany today. Bare with me this might be long but I gotta get it off my chest. As silly as it may be or sound to others it makes total sense to me and hopefully will make sense to others.... (1 of 15)

But we were considered essential workers but lost our "hero pay" because this company didn't wanna pay their workers extra. We got treated like shit by customers due to no toilet paper and for other shit we can't control! All because everyone wanted to horde shit. (8 of 9)

And I don't want anything else. This place has been ruined for me and nothing will ever bring back that love I had for this job when I started. Don't get me wrong. I'm grateful for a job when so many lost theirs in 2020 due to the pandemic. (7 of 9)

But not enough time. It's a little too late for transparency now. It's too late to offer me something better here. You can offer me a pay raise for me to only cap at a certain amount and never make more. I don't want a lead position. Don't want manager. (6 of 9)

So I get to suffer while you hire on a new person for my department I want rather then putting them in my department and training them and moving me? You're willing to accommodate a co-worker with less seniority's hours because they have a 2nd job but I don't get that? (3 of 9)
